name: NV Attorney General
tweet: #NCPW2022 Online shopping scams are the most common type of scams according to the Better Business Bureau 2021 Scam Tracker Report. These scams start with a fake website, mobile app or social media ad. Always verify you're shopping at a legitimate online retailer.

name: NV Attorney General
tweet: #NCPW2022 Tip: If you receive a phone call from your financial institution asking for your personal information or to confirm your identity, hang up and call them directly. Better to be safe than sorry! #ConsumerProtection

name: NV Attorney General
tweet: #NCPW2022 Tip: As a consumer, you have a right to obtain a copy of an entire contract for goods or services.  Read through contracts carefully, and consider consulting with a private attorney. Don’t sign contracts hastily or without reading and understanding them.

name: NV Attorney General
tweet: #NCPW2022 Tip: Scams common to social media can involve identity theft — stealing another person's personal information.  Examples include surveys or contests requesting personal information and catfishing (posing as a friend with the intent of taking money or personal info).

name: NV Attorney General
tweet: There’s nothing a student loan debt relief company can do that you can’t do yourself, especially with the help of your student loan servicer. If a debt relief offer from a private company seems too good to be true, it probably is. #NCPW2022   https://t.co/Ok4AlZB4t8  https://t.co/7ox6moBxsB

tweet: HAPPENING NOW | @NevadaAG @AaronDFordNV  chairs today's meeting of the Statewide Substance Use Response Working Group, which works to develop recommendations to improve Nevada's substance use prevention and response.  You can view the meeting online here:   https://t.co/3YI8vD9FFD

name: NV Attorney General
tweet: #NCPW2022 Tip: Verify celebrity accounts that you follow on TikTok or other social media.    Avoid impostors that want to promote investment opportunities or other scams. A quick way to verify accounts is to do an internet search for the celebrity’s name and “TikTok.”

name: NV Attorney General
tweet: NV Atty General Aaron D. Ford released a statement regarding his office’s position on potential price gouging as gas prices increase due to global supply chain issues. If you suspect or have info about price gouging, file a complaint with the AG's Office.  https://t.co/khCoSVnTuT  https://t.co/7Xv1KJt1o1

name: NV Attorney General
tweet: #NCPW2022 Tip: Don’t be fooled by notarios and other consultants who promise immediate results or solutions.   Many scammers posing as notarios cost more than licensed attorneys! If you aren't sure someone is qualified, ask for proof of their credentials and retain a copy.

name: NV Attorney General
tweet: Today, on #InternationalWomensDay, we celebrate the many incredible women around the world that contribute so much to our society.   Your AG's Office will always stand up for the equal rights of women, and work to affirm and uphold the rights fought for by women trailblazers.

name: NV Attorney General
tweet: Be cautious when choosing a COVID-19 vaccination or testing service. Some providers may be imposters. Don't give any financial or medical information to an unverified provider. COVID-19 vaccines are FREE! If anyone charges you for the vaccine it's a scam. #NCPW2022  https://t.co/YuTaZzxG0w

name: NV Attorney General
tweet: SHARE | Nevada Attorney General Aaron D. Ford advises Nevadans to be on alert for novel tech scams.  #ConsumerProtection #NCPW2022  https://t.co/Wx7ju5eyf4

name: NV Attorney General
tweet: #NCPW2022 Tip: Be aware of pressure tactics.  Door to door sales, urgent texts and evening phone calls all have one thing in common — they are pressure tactics designed to drive consumers to impulsive decisions. Always take your time, or simply don’t respond to pressure tactics.

name: NV Attorney General
tweet: New to NFTs (non-fungible tokens)? Beware of fraudulent NFT stores or someone telling you that you've "won" an NFT. Verification is key! #NCPW2022 #consumerprotection  https://t.co/E42Lo6N72j

name: NV Attorney General
tweet: #NCPW2022 Tip: If a deal sounds too good to be true, it probably is.  Remember: when signing a contract, anything you were promised must be included in writing. Review contracts carefully, ask questions and don’t feel pressured into signing anything you haven't read.
